LongDescription:
The Moxella Class destroyer is a highly capable scout and escort vessel in use with the Falcatan Navy. Initially devoloped in cooperation with engineers from the Shelter Alliance, it incorporates many elements of their naval design. When relations broke apart in 462 IY, the class, still in its early stages, was completed by Falcata alone. 

Despite their utilitarian appearance, the Moxella's are undoubtedly the fastest ships in FRN service. An oversized drive section lends them both their speed, and a level of survivability astonishingly high for a ship of such a meagre weight class.
FlavorText:
"These girls aren't without their problems; the nature of their electrical system necessitated an obstructive placement of the main comms antenna. They sacrifice some serious firepower for those drives, and just because they can take a beating doesnt mean that beating is fun to recieve. I needed new pants after a skirmish with pirates a few years back, a big ass shell went right through my computer monitor, straight over my head!

But ill be damned if anyone takes me off of my baby, she FLIES. Their aint a lot of ships in space whre you really *feel* the accelleration, but this is one of them. A good pilot will keep you out of trouble thick or thin, I proved that myself dodging the missile rain out at Sierra Natura- and i'll do it again, Shelter be damned."

- A. Kamal, Helmsman
